      "comments": [
        {
          "author_name": "Peter Ovchynnikov",
          "author_url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/ovchyn",
          "text": "On the Biology of a LLM\nhttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=PwAcQTyZZ7I",
          "reactions": 1,
          "replies_count": 0
        },
        {
          "author_name": "Andrii Rozhylo",
          "author_url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/arozhylo",
          "text": "When you work a lot with models, with time, a certain internal feeling appears, as if you already know in advance what response will come from the system, so you adjust your prompt in a way that steers that response in the direction you need.\n\nHope is what drives us when we launch a new AI process for the first time. But after a few iterations this feeling starts to emerge. \n\nLook deeper within yourself 🧘😇",
          "reactions": 1,
          "replies_count": 1
        },
        {
          "author_name": "Kate Chapman",
          "author_url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/untanglingsystems",
          "text": "This very point of we can't understand why it does things leads me down the path of does that mean it is conscious? I haven't decided yet.",
          "reactions": 1,
          "replies_count": 0
        },
        {
          "author_name": "Gianluigi Fliri",
          "author_url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/gianluigi-fliri",
          "text": "In the eighties researchers hypothized that neural networks could one day produce intelligent behaviour. Back then they only could run tiny perceptrons, but the intuition was there. In recent years it has been proved right. So I believe that, yes, we don't fully understand the magic, but it doesn't come from pure empirism. It is by design.",
          "reactions": 1,
          "replies_count": 1
        },
        {
          "author_name": "jerome SUSGIN",
          "author_url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/jerome-susgin-b06b3b174",
          "text": "We know what LLM are : a stochastic generator of words (token) given a context (a prompt and the trained weights).",
          "reactions": 0,
          "replies_count": 1
        }
      ]
